The paper discusses the use of bug finding tools in software development, which falls under the category of software engineering (cs.SE). The paper also mentions static analysis, which is a technique used in programming languages (cs.PL). The comparison of bug finding tools with reviews and tests involves evaluating the effectiveness of different methods for detecting defects in software, which relates to the field of computer security (cs.CR). The case study mentioned in the paper involves analyzing several projects, which could fall under the category of software development (cs.SD). Finally, the paper discusses the use of automation in reducing the time spent on testing and review activities, which could relate to the field of machine learning (cs.LG).
